ChatGPT said:
To use a module from the Terraform Registry, follow these steps. For this example, letâ€™s use a Google Cloud VM instance module from the registry.

âœ… Step 1: Find a Registry Module
Visit: https://registry.terraform.io/modules

Search for something like:
ðŸ“¦ terraform-google-modules/vm/google

âœ… Step 2: Add the Module to main.tf
Add a block like this in your main.tf:

module "vm_from_registry" {
source = "terraform-google-modules/vm/google"
version = "~> 7.9.0"

project_id = var.project_id
region = var.region
zone = var.zone
name = "registry-vm"
instance_count = 1
machine_type = "e2-medium"
source_image_family = "debian-11"
source_image_project = "debian-cloud"
subnetwork = "default"
}
This uses a public module that deploys VM instances with flexible options.

âœ… Step 3: Initialize and Apply
terraform init
terraform apply -auto-approve
This will create a VM using the public module. You can explore the moduleâ€™s full input options at the Terraform Registry page.

